    "extras": [
      "June to September is the easiest all-round window for this route, while December to March is best only if you want frozen-canal, Christmas market, or ski-season energy.",
      "Reserve Banff Gondola, Lake Louise shuttles, and summer Rockies hotels as soon as dates are fixed — the best-value slots disappear first.",
      "Greyhound no longer operates domestically in most of Canada, so FlixBus is the easiest coach substitute when you want to save versus VIA Rail.",
      "Carry a light waterproof layer even in summer; Vancouver rain and Rockies temperature swings can hit the same trip.",
      "If you want a cheaper Rockies stay, sleep in Canmore and day-trip into Banff by Roam Transit or car."
    ],
